description:
Mirror POST /api/identity for a NAME claim. Client does GET /api/challenge, signs a DOMAIN-SEPARATED canonical message binding the nonce to the claim ('mjolnir-name-claim:v1
{challenge}
{name}
{port}') so a captured identity-ceremony signature can't be replayed as a name claim and a MITM can't rebind the name. Server verifies Ed25519, validates the name (normalized single DNS label via mjolnir_mesh::normalize_device_host, not reserved), consumes the nonce, and spools {pubkey}.json into spool_dir/names/ (subdir so meshd's *.json identity sweep ignores it). The spooled record carries pubkey+sig+challenge+name+port so a later stage can put the SIGNATURE into the gossiped CRDT for mesh-wide verification. THIS SLICE = auth only.

value:
Key-owned .mesh names (epic mjolnir-mesh-coo): authority = client Ed25519 keypair, NOT node. Name-claim signs a domain-separated message 'mjolnir-name-claim:v1
{challenge}
{name}
{port}' (prevents replaying an identity-ceremony signature). The signature is CARRIED INTO the gossiped CRDT and re-verified on every node (name lane is trustless — unlike /users which trusts the ingesting node). Ownership is a renewable LEASE that fades to reclaimable (reverses e21.2.2 D-004 permanent tombstone) so a lost key never locks a name. Two-tier fade: ephemeral liveness (~60s, stops resolving) + durable HLC lease expiry (hours, governs cross-key reclaim). One name per key. Reputation/tenure deferred to d0w.
